A mammal of the camel family that is the hybrid offspring of a llama and a guanaco.
A plainsman; a South American cattle-herder or cowboy, especially in Venezuela and Colombia.
(Texas) A plain or steppe in parts of Latin America.
(historical) A colorful turban worn by the Sapa Incas.

n: The German name given to several Ice Age plateaux in the Havelland region, which climb to over 70 meters above the formerly marshy urstromtal levels (old glacial meltwater valleys) of the Havelland Luch and the Rhinluch.
An Austrian folk dance in the form of a slow waltz.

w: An uncommon bichon bred in North-Western Europe.
l: (mineralogy) An iron arsenide mineral often found with arsenopyrite.

b: A native or inhabitant of Lübeck.

e: (mineralogy) A dark-green igneous rock consisting largely of chrysolite, with pyroxene and picotite.
